{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876794829,"sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8164ff001ChIAvTvUea0p9T","messageID":"msg_d7a815df9001u3eBbOiUscp6Y6","sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d1f8f18b8307446587473675","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** root\n4: > **Language:** Makefile\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-033/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-033/design.md`, `changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** <!-- TODO: List dependencies or None -->\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: <!-- TODO: Add tasks -->\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Dependency Graph\n17: \n18: <!-- TODO: Add dependency graph -->\n19: \n20: ## Parallelizable Groups\n21: \n22: <!-- TODO: Add parallelizable groups -->\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Acceptance Criteria\n27: \n28: <!-- TODO: Add acceptance criteria -->\n29: \n30: | # | Criterion | Command |\n31: |---|-----------|---------|\n32: | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** root\n> **Language:** Makefile\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-033/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-033/design.md`, `changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** <!-- TODO: List dependencies or None -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- TODO: Add tasks -->\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n<!-- TODO: Add dependency graph -->\n\n## Parallelizable Groups","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775876794822,"end":1775876794828}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876796057,"sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","part":{"id":"prt_d7a816a580012NVjehnWHL6J9m","messageID":"msg_d7a815df9001u3eBbOiUscp6Y6","sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_129172ec048a4092b10720ad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the HTTP client layer of the AgentCube Python SDK — session creation with connection pooling, control plane and data plane HTTP client contracts, header management, timeout behavior, error handling, and utility functions.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## HTTP Session Factory\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: create_session\n19: The system SHALL provide a `create_session` function that returns a `requests.Session` configured with connection pooling.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: default pool parameters\n22: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called with no arguments\n23: - **WHEN** the session is created\n24: - **THEN** `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` SHALL be mounted for both `http://` and `https://` prefixes\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: custom pool parameters\n27: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n28: - **WHEN** the session is created\n29: - **THEN** both adapters SHALL use the provided pool parameters\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## ControlPlaneClient\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient constructor\n36: The system SHALL initialize `ControlPlaneClient` with URL resolution from arguments or environment, and auth token resolution from arguments or ServiceAccount file.\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: base URL from argument\n39: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")`\n40: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n41: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm:8080\"`\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: base URL from environment\n44: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` is `None` and env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n45: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n46: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: auth token from argument\n49: - **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"my-token\"` is provided\n50: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n51: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer my-token\"`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: auth token from ServiceAccount file\n54: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` or empty and file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists with content `\"sa-token\\n\"`\n55: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n56: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer sa-token\"`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: auth token file not found\n59: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` and the ServiceAccount token file does not exist\n60: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n61: - **THEN** `read_token_from_file` returns `\"\"` and `Authorization` header SHALL NOT be set\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: empty token skips Authorization header\n64: - **GIVEN** resolved token is empty string\n65: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n66: - **THEN** `session.headers` SHALL NOT contain `Authorization`\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: default Content-Type header\n69: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n70: - **WHEN** session headers are inspected\n71: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Content-Type\"]` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: default timeout parameters\n74: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called with no timeout arguments\n75: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n76: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.create_session\n79: The system SHALL POST to the Workload Manager to create a Code Interpreter session and return the session ID.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: successful session creation\n82: - **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=7200, metadata={\"key\": \"val\"})`\n83: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n84: - **THEN** `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"ns\", \"ttl\": 7200, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"val\"}}`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: response contains sessionId\n87: - **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}}`\n88: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n89: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: response missing sessionId\n92: - **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {}}`\n93: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n94: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `ValueError`\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: request timeout tuple\n97: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n98: - **WHEN** any request is sent\n99: - **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session\n102: The system SHALL DELETE a session and treat 404 as success.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: successful deletion\n105: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 200\n106: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n107: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: 404 treated as success\n110: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent\")` returns HTTP 404\n111: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n112: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: other error logged and returns False\n115: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 500\n116: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n117: - **THEN** the method SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.close\n120: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: close releases session\n123: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.close()` is called\n124: - **WHEN** the method executes\n125: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructor\n132: The system SHALL initialize the data plane client with base URL derived from router URL or explicit `base_url`.\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: base URL from router URL\n135: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")`\n136: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n137: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"`\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: base URL explicit override\n140: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom/url/\")`\n141: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n142: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://custom/url/\"` and router/namespace/cr_name SHALL be ignored for URL construction\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: session header set\n145: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n146: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n147: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` SHALL be `\"sess-1\"`\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: default timeouts\n150: - **GIVEN** no timeout arguments provided\n151: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n152: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: _request method\n155: The system SHALL send HTTP requests with appropriate headers based on whether a body is present.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: JSON body request\n158: - **GIVEN** `_request(\"POST\", \"api/execute\", body=b'{\"cmd\": \"ls\"}')`\n159: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n160: - **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be set on the request and URL SHALL be `urljoin(self.base_url, \"api/execute\")`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: request without body\n163: - **GIVEN** `_request(\"GET\", \"api/files\")`\n164: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n165: - **THEN** no `Content-Type` override SHALL be set (session defaults apply)\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: execute_command\n168: The system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with command and timeout, adding a 2-second buffer to read timeout.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: command with explicit timeout\n171: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=10.0)`\n172: - **WHEN** the request is built\n173: - **THEN** HTTP read timeout SHALL be `12.0` (`timeout + 2.0`) and body SHALL contain `{\"command\": [\"sleep 10\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"}`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: command with default timeout\n176: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls\", timeout=None)` and `self.timeout` is `120`\n177: - **WHEN** the request is built\n178: - **THEN** effective timeout SHALL be `120` and body SHALL contain `\"timeout\": \"120s\"`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: command string split into list\n181: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\")`\n182: - **WHEN** the body is constructed\n183: - **THEN** `command` field SHALL be `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (split by whitespace)\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: non-zero exit code raises error\n186: - **GIVEN** response JSON is `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error\", \"stdout\": \"\"}`\n187: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n188: - **THEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=\"ls\")` SHALL be raised\n189: \n190: ### Requirement: run_code\n191: The system SHALL write code to a timestamped file and execute it via the interpreter.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Python code execution\n194: - **GIVEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hi')\")`\n195: - **WHEN** the method executes\n196: - **THEN** it SHALL call `write_file` with a timestamped `.py` file, then `execute_command(\"python3 <file>\")`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: language alias normalization\n199: - **GIVEN** `language` is `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n200: - **WHEN** `run_code` executes\n201: - **THEN** it SHALL be treated as Python and follow the same path as `\"python\"`\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: write_file\n204: The system SHALL POST base64-encoded content to `api/files`.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: write file with base64 content\n207: - **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")`\n208: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n209: - **THEN** POST `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'hello'>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n210: \n211: ### Requirement: upload_file\n212: The system SHALL POST multipart form data to `api/files` with session header.\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: multipart upload\n215: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")`\n216: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n217: - **THEN** POST `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/path.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id` explicitly set\n218: \n219: ### Requirement: download_file\n220: The system SHALL GET file content with streaming and write to local path.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: streaming download\n223: - **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path.txt\", \"/local/out.txt\")`\n224: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n225: - **THEN** GET `api/files/remote/path.txt` (with `lstrip(\"/\")`), `stream=True`, and content SHALL be written in chunks to `/local/out.txt`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: clean path strips leading slash\n228: - **GIVEN** `remote_path = \"/absolute/path.txt\"`\n229: - **WHEN** download URL is constructed\n230: - **THEN** `clean_path` SHALL be `\"absolute/path.txt\"`\n231: \n232: ### Requirement: list_files\n233: The system SHALL GET file listing with path query parameter.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: list files in path\n236: - **GIVEN** `list_files(\"/some/path\")`\n237: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n238: - **THEN** GET `api/files?path=/some/path`\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close\n241: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: close releases session\n244: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n245: - **WHEN** the method executes\n246: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructor\n253: The system SHALL initialize the agent runtime data plane client with invocation base URL.\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: base URL construction\n256: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")`\n257: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n258: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"`\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: SESSION_HEADER class constant\n261: - **GIVEN** the class definition\n262: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER` is accessed\n263: - **THEN** the value SHALL be `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: bootstrap_session_id\n266: The system SHALL GET the invocation base URL and extract session ID from response header.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: session ID extracted from header\n269: - **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` returns response with header `x-agentcube-session-id: \"new-session\"`\n270: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"new-session\"`\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: missing session ID header raises error\n274: - **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` response does not contain `x-agentcube-session-id`\n275: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n277: \n278: ### Requirement: invoke\n279: The system SHALL POST JSON payload to the invocation base URL with session header.\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: invoke with session header\n282: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s1\", payload={\"msg\": \"hello\"})`\n283: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n284: - **THEN** POST `{base_url}` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: s1` and `Content-Type: application/json`, body SHALL be JSON `{\"msg\": \"hello\"}`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: invoke with default timeout\n287: - **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=None)`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `self.timeout=120`\n288: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n289: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: invoke with custom timeout\n292: - **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=60.0)`\n293: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n294: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 60.0)`\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: invoke without session_id raises error\n297: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty string\n298: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n299: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close\n302: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: close releases session\n305: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n306: - **WHEN** the method executes\n307: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Connection Pool Reuse\n312: \n313: ### Requirement: Session reuse within client\n314: The system SHALL reuse a single `requests.Session` instance per client for all HTTP operations.\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: same session for multiple requests\n317: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` calls `create_session` then `delete_session`\n318: - **WHEN** both requests are sent\n319: - **THEN** they SHALL use the same `self.session` instance\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: independent sessions across clients\n322: - **GIVEN** two `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instances are created\n323: - **WHEN** their session objects are compared\n324: - **THEN** `client1.session` and `client2.session` SHALL be different objects\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Utility Functions\n329: \n330: ### Requirement: read_token_from_file\n331: The system SHALL read and strip token content from a file, returning empty string on missing file.\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: file exists with trailing newline\n334: - **GIVEN** file `/tmp/token` contains `\"my-token\\n\"`\n335: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` is called\n336: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-token\"`\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: file not found\n339: - **GIVEN** file `/tmp/nonexistent` does not exist\n340: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/nonexistent\")` is called\n341: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"\"`\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: get_logger\n344: The system SHALL create a named logger with configurable level.\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: logger with custom level\n347: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_module\", level=\"DEBUG\")`\n348: - **WHEN** the function executes\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Logger named `\"test_module\"` with level `DEBUG`\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Exception Hierarchy\n354: \n355: ### Requirement: Exception classes\n356: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n359: - **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"err\", command=\"ls\")`\n360: - **WHEN** the exception is created\n361: - **THEN** `exc.exit_code` SHALL be `1`, `exc.stderr` SHALL be `\"err\"`, `exc.command` SHALL be `\"ls\"`, and `str(exc)` SHALL contain `\"Command failed (exit 1): err\"`\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: exception inheritance\n364: - **GIVEN** the exception classes are defined\n365: - **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n366: - **THEN** `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` SHALL all be subclasses of `AgentCubeError`\n\n(End of file - total 366 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the HTTP client layer of the AgentCube Python SDK — session creation with connection pooling, control plane and data plane HTTP client contracts, header management, timeout behavior, error handling, and utility functions.\n\n---\n\n## HTTP Session Factory\n\n### Requirement: create_session\nThe system SHALL provide a `create_session` function that returns a `requests.Session` configured with connection pooling.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876796047,"end":1775876796054}}}}
