{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775876804646,"sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","part":{"id":"prt_d7a819023001VtBQPSXfNKWJgj","messageID":"msg_d7a818c15001Po2NZs8yPvntec","sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876879019,"sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","part":{"id":"prt_d7a819dfc001fEpozPeiMwguzm","messageID":"msg_d7a818c15001Po2NZs8yPvntec","sessionID":"ses_28580d662ffeyNGTIvNO1GV5Sf","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_2b78d4317159424c8127c6a5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `root`\n- **Language:** Makefile\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the creation of a root-level `Makefile` for the AgentCube project, providing a unified entry point for building Go binaries, Docker images, running tests, linting, and Helm operations. The Makefile SHALL orchestrate existing tooling (go, docker, helm, golangci-lint) without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n\n---\n\n## Variables and Configuration\n\n### Requirement: Default variable values\nThe Makefile SHALL define the following variables with default values that can be overridden by the caller:\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `TAG` | `latest` | Docker image tag |\n| `REGISTRY` | `agentcube` | Docker image registry prefix |\n| `GOOS` | `$(shell go env GOOS)` | Target operating system |\n| `GOARCH` | `$(shell go env GOARCH)` | Target architecture |\n| `BIN_DIR` | `bin` | Binary output directory |\n| `LDFLAGS` | `-s -w` | Linker flags (strip debug + compress) |\n| `VERBOSE` | (empty) | Set to `1` to enable verbose command output |\n\n#### Scenario: TAG override\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make docker TAG=v0.1.0`\n- **WHEN** Docker images are built\n- **THEN** the image tag SHALL be `v0.1.0` instead of `latest`\n\n#### Scenario: REGISTRY override\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make docker REGISTRY=myregistry.io/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** Docker images are built\n- **THEN** image names SHALL be prefixed with `myregistry.io/agentcube/`\n\n#### Scenario: Cross-compilation via GOOS/GOARCH\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make build GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64`\n- **WHEN** Go binaries are compiled\n- **THEN** `GOOS=linux` and `GOARCH=arm64` SHALL be passed to `go build`\n\n#### Scenario: VERBOSE enables command echo\n- **GIVEN** `VERBOSE=1` is set\n- **WHEN** any target executes\n- **THEN** the underlying commands SHALL be printed before execution\n\n#### Scenario: VERBOSE=0 suppresses command echo\n- **GIVEN** `VERBOSE` is not set or is empty\n- **WHEN** any target executes\n- **THEN** the underlying commands SHALL NOT be printed (silent by default)\n\n---\n\n## Go Build Targets\n\n### Requirement: build\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `build` target that compiles all Go binaries to `$(BIN_DIR)/`. The binaries SHALL be: `router`, `workloadmanager`, `agentd`, `picod`.\n\n#### Scenario: build compiles all binaries\n- **GIVEN** the project root contains `cmd/router/`, `cmd/workloadmanager/`, `cmd/agentd/`, `cmd/picod/`\n- **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n- **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/router`, `$(BIN_DIR)/workloadmanager`, `$(BIN_DIR)/agentd`, and `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL exist as executable files\n\n#### Scenario: build uses LDFLAGS\n- **GIVEN** `LDFLAGS` is set to `-s -w`\n- **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n- **THEN** `go build` SHALL be invoked with `-ldflags '-s -w'`\n\n#### Scenario: build applies GOOS/GOARCH\n- **GIVEN** `make build GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64` is executed\n- **WHEN** the binaries are compiled\n- **THEN** all output binaries SHALL be built for `linux/amd64`\n\n### Requirement: build/<binary>\nThe Makefile SHALL provide per-binary build targets in the form `build/<binary>` for each of: `router`, `workloadmanager`, `agentd`, `picod`.\n\n#### Scenario: build/router compiles only router\n- **GIVEN** `make build/router` is executed\n- **WHEN** the build completes\n- **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/router` SHALL exist\n- **AND** `$(BIN_DIR)/workloadmanager`, `$(BIN_DIR)/agentd`, `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL NOT be created by this invocation\n\n#### Scenario: build/picod compiles only picod\n- **GIVEN** `make build/picod` is executed\n- **WHEN** the build completes\n- **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: build/<binary> uses correct package path\n- **GIVEN** `make build/router` is executed\n- **WHEN** the build command is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` (not `./cmd/` or any other path)\n\n### Requirement: clean\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `clean` target that removes the `$(BIN_DIR)/` directory and all build artifacts.\n\n#### Scenario: clean removes bin directory\n- **GIVEN** `make build` has been run and `$(BIN_DIR)/` exists with binaries\n- **WHEN** `make clean` is executed\n- **THEN** the `$(BIN_DIR)/` directory SHALL be removed\n\n#### Scenario: clean is idempotent\n- **GIVEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `make clean` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL succeed without error\n\n---\n\n## Docker Build Targets\n\n### Requirement: docker\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `docker` target that builds all Docker images: `agentcube` (from `docker/Dockerfile`), `router` (from `docker/Dockerfile.router`), and `picod` (from `docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n\n#### Scenario: docker builds all images\n- **GIVEN** `make docker TAG=latest REGISTRY=agentcube` is executed\n- **WHEN** the build completes\n- **THEN** the following images SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon:\n  - `agentcube/agentcube:latest`\n  - `agentcube/router:latest`\n  - `agentcube/picod:latest`\n\n#### Scenario: docker uses correct Dockerfiles\n- **GIVEN** `make docker` is executed\n- **WHEN** the docker build commands are inspected\n- **THEN** the agentcube image SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile`, router SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.router`, and picod SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n\n#### Scenario: docker applies TAG variable\n- **GIVEN** `make docker TAG=v0.2.0` is executed\n- **WHEN** the build completes\n- **THEN** all images SHALL be tagged with `v0.2.0` (e.g., `agentcube/agentcube:v0.2.0`)\n\n#### Scenario: docker applies REGISTRY variable\n- **GIVEN** `make docker REGISTRY=ghcr.io/myorg` is executed\n- **WHEN** the build completes\n- **THEN** image names SHALL be prefixed with `ghcr.io/myorg/` (e.g., `ghcr.io/myorg/router:latest`)\n\n### Requirement: docker/<image>\nThe Makefile SHALL provide per-image build targets in the form `docker/<image>` for each of: `agentcube`, `router`, `picod`.\n\n#### Scenario: docker/router builds only router image\n- **GIVEN** `make docker/router TAG=latest` is executed\n- **WHEN** the build completes\n- **THEN** `agentcube/router:latest` SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon\n- **AND** `agentcube/agentcube:latest` and `agentcube/picod:latest` SHALL NOT be built by this invocation\n\n#### Scenario: docker/picod uses correct Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `make docker/picod` is executed\n- **WHEN** the docker build command is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.picod` with the project root as build context\n\n---\n\n## Test Targets\n\n### Requirement: test\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `test` target that runs all Go unit tests.\n\n#### Scenario: test runs all Go tests\n- **GIVEN** `make test` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `go test ./...` SHALL have been executed\n- **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect test pass/fail (non-zero on failure)\n\n### Requirement: test-coverage\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `test-coverage` target that runs Go tests with coverage profiling and writes the output to `coverage.out`.\n\n#### Scenario: test-coverage generates coverage report\n- **GIVEN** `make test-coverage` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL exist in the project root\n- **AND** the file SHALL contain valid Go coverage data (parseable by `go tool cover`)\n\n#### Scenario: test-coverage covers all packages\n- **GIVEN** `make test-coverage` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `-coverprofile=coverage.out` flag\n\n### Requirement: test-chart\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `test-chart` target that runs the Helm chart render test script.\n\n#### Scenario: test-chart executes render script\n- **GIVEN** `make test-chart` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `bash test/chart/test_render.sh` SHALL have been executed\n- **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect the script's pass/fail status\n\n---\n\n## Code Quality Targets\n\n### Requirement: lint\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `lint` target that runs `golangci-lint`.\n\n#### Scenario: lint runs golangci-lint\n- **GIVEN** `make lint` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `golangci-lint run` SHALL have been executed\n- **AND** the exit code SHALL be non-zero if lint violations are found\n\n### Requirement: fmt\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `fmt` target that formats Go source code.\n\n#### Scenario: fmt formats all Go files\n- **GIVEN** `make fmt` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `go fmt ./...` SHALL have been executed\n- **AND** any unformatted Go files SHALL be reformatted in place\n\n### Requirement: vet\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `vet` target that runs Go's static analyzer.\n\n#### Scenario: vet runs go vet\n- **GIVEN** `make vet` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `go vet ./...` SHALL have been executed\n- **AND** the exit code SHALL be non-zero if vet issues are found\n\n---\n\n## Helm Targets\n\n### Requirement: helm-lint\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `helm-lint` target that validates Helm charts.\n\n#### Scenario: helm-lint validates charts\n- **GIVEN** `make helm-lint` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `helm lint manifests/` (or the appropriate chart path) SHALL have been executed\n- **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect lint pass/fail\n\n### Requirement: helm-template\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `helm-template` target that renders Helm templates for inspection.\n\n#### Scenario: helm-template outputs rendered manifests\n- **GIVEN** `make helm-template` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `helm template` SHALL output the rendered Kubernetes manifests to stdout\n- **AND** the command SHALL NOT modify any files (read-only operation)\n\n---\n\n## Python Targets\n\n### Requirement: python-lint\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `python-lint` target that runs Python linting tools against the SDK/CLI code, gracefully handling the case where tools are not installed.\n\n#### Scenario: python-lint runs ruff when available\n- **GIVEN** `ruff` is installed and `make python-lint` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `ruff check` (or equivalent) SHALL have been run against the Python SDK/CLI source\n\n#### Scenario: python-lint succeeds when tools are absent\n- **GIVEN** neither `ruff` nor `flake8` is installed and `make python-lint` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** the target SHALL succeed (exit 0) with a warning message indicating no lint tool was found\n\n### Requirement: python-test\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `python-test` target that runs Python tests, gracefully handling the case where pytest is not installed.\n\n#### Scenario: python-test runs pytest when available\n- **GIVEN** `pytest` is installed and `make python-test` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `pytest` SHALL have been run against the Python SDK/CLI test directory\n\n#### Scenario: python-test succeeds when pytest is absent\n- **GIVEN** `pytest` is not installed and `make python-test` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** the target SHALL succeed (exit 0) with a warning message indicating pytest was not found\n\n---\n\n## Composite Targets\n\n### Requirement: all\nThe Makefile SHALL provide an `all` target that serves as the default target and runs a complete local development verification.\n\n#### Scenario: all runs build, test, and lint\n- **GIVEN** `make` (or `make all`) is executed with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `make build`, `make test`, and `make lint` SHALL all have been executed\n- **AND** execution SHALL stop on the first failure (non-zero exit code)\n\n### Requirement: ci\nThe Makefile SHALL provide a `ci` target that runs the full CI gate verification suite.\n\n#### Scenario: ci runs full CI gate\n- **GIVEN** `make ci` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** `make build`, `make test`, `make test-coverage`, `make lint`, and `make helm-lint` SHALL all have been executed\n- **AND** execution SHALL stop on the first failure\n\n#### Scenario: ci produces coverage output\n- **GIVEN** `make ci` is executed\n- **WHEN** the command completes successfully\n- **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL exist in the project root\n\n---\n\n## Phony Targets\n\n### Requirement: .PHONY declaration\nAll non-file-producing targets SHALL be declared as `.PHONY` to prevent conflicts with files of the same name.\n\n#### Scenario: all targets are phony\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile is parsed\n- **WHEN** `.PHONY` declarations are inspected\n- **THEN** the following targets SHALL be declared `.PHONY`:\n  `all`, `build`, `clean`, `test`, `test-coverage`, `test-chart`, `lint`, `fmt`, `vet`,\n  `docker`, `helm-lint`, `helm-template`, `python-lint`, `python-test`, `ci`,\n  and all `build/<binary>` and `docker/<image>` targets\n\n#### Scenario: phony targets work even if同名 files exist\n- **GIVEN** a file named `build` exists in the project root\n- **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n- **THEN** the Makefile target SHALL execute (not treat `build` as a file dependency)\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Requirement: Build failure propagation\nWhen any sub-command in a target fails, the Makefile SHALL propagate the non-zero exit code.\n\n#### Scenario: go build failure stops build\n- **GIVEN** a Go source file contains a compilation error\n- **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL exit with a non-zero status\n- **AND** no further binaries SHALL be built after the failure\n\n#### Scenario: test failure stops ci\n- **GIVEN** a Go test is failing\n- **WHEN** `make ci` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL exit with a non-zero status after `make test` fails\n- **AND** `make lint` and `make helm-lint` SHALL NOT be executed\n\n### Requirement: Missing tool graceful handling\nTargets that depend on external tools (golangci-lint, helm, ruff, pytest) SHALL fail with a clear error message when the tool is not found, except for Python targets which SHALL warn and succeed.\n\n#### Scenario: golangci-lint missing causes lint failure\n- **GIVEN** `golangci-lint` is not installed\n- **WHEN** `make lint` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL fail with a message indicating `golangci-lint` is required\n\n#### Scenario: helm missing causes helm-lint failure\n- **GIVEN** `helm` is not installed\n- **WHEN** `make helm-lint` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL fail with a message indicating `helm` is required\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Create | `Makefile` | Root-level Makefile with all build, test, docker, lint, helm, and python targets |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876879000,"end":1775876879016}}}}
